## Data Flows

### Ingestion Flow
1. User uploads document via Chainlit UI
2. Raw file stored to Azure Blob Storage
3. LangChain loader parses file → text chunks
4. Chunks embedded and stored in Qdrant vector store
5. Document metadata (filename, date, tags) stored in PostgreSQL
6. Full trace logged to LangSmith

### Chat Flow
1. User sends message via Chainlit
2. LangGraph orchestrator receives message
3. Retrieves recent conversation history from PostgreSQL
4. Semantic search on Qdrant for relevant doc chunks
5. Builds context window: system prompt + user profile + history + retrieved chunks
6. Claude generates response
7. Response returned to Chainlit UI
8. Full conversation turn saved to PostgreSQL
9. Full trace logged to LangSmith

### Memory Update Flow
1. After each conversation session ends
2. LangGraph runs memory extraction pass over the session
3. Claude extracts key facts, preferences, decisions, style cues
4. New facts merged into user profile in PostgreSQL (dedup + update)
5. Updated profile injected into system prompt for next session

