## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Mac mini M4 (or any Mac/Linux machine)
- Docker Desktop installed
- Python 3.11+
- Anthropic API key — [console.anthropic.com](https://console.anthropic.com)
- LangSmith API key — [smith.langchain.com](https://smith.langchain.com) (free)

### 1. Run the setup script
```bash
chmod +x setup-mac-mini.sh
./setup-mac-mini.sh
```

### 2. Fill in your API keys
```bash
cp .env.example .env
nano .env
```

### 3. Start local services
```bash
docker compose up -d
```

### 4. Verify services are running
```bash
docker compose ps
curl http://localhost:6333/healthz    # Qdrant
docker exec second_brain_postgres pg_isready -U brain_user
```

### 5. Run the app
```bash
source .venv/bin/activate
chainlit run interface/app.py
```

Open [http://localhost:8000](http://localhost:8000) in your browser.

